    <stitle>DT-466E and 530E Diesel Engine Diagnostics Model Years 1999-2000 - ELECTRONIC CONTROL SYSTEM DIAGNOSTICS -
        Circuit Function And Diagnostics - Injection Control Pressure Sensor (ICP)
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="troubleshoot" graphiccount="4">
        <title>Injection Control Pressure Sensor (ICP)</title>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Signal Functions</title>
            <figure id="f17503063" figsize="pg-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figEG1/EG1239A.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="352px" box="no"/>
                <caption>Function Diagram for Injection Control Pressure Sensor</caption>
            </figure>
            <para>The Injection Control Pressure (ICP) sensor is a variable capacitance sensor that when supplied with a
                5V reference signal from the ECM produces a linear analog voltage signal that indicates pressure.
            </para>
            <para>The ICP sensor's primary function is to provide a feedback signal to indicate injection control
                pressure. This enables the ECM to command the correct injector timing and pulse width and the correct
                injection control pressure for proper fuel delivery at all speed and load conditions.
            </para>
        </svcsubproc>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Fault Detection / Management</title>
            <para>If the ECM detects a malfunctioning ICP sensor or a problem in the ICP sensor circuit, the WARN ENGINE
                lamp will illuminate. The ECM will go to open loop control of injection control pressure (operate from
                an estimated ICP pressure).
            </para>
